               <floruit>He was a learned man and writer in his mother tongue, Tǝgre, and the most important informant of <persName ref="PRS6324Littmann">Littmann</persName>, the then head of
                  Princeton university expedition for Tǝgre language. He was a muslim and later converted to Protestantism. Having converted to Christianity,
                  <persName ref="PRS7453NaffaW">Naffāʿ Wad ʿƎtmān</persName>, himself became a teacher and a missionary in <date>1901</date>.
                  Besides, he began to collect and write the tradition of his people. He met <persName ref="PRS6324Littmann">Littmann</persName> in <date>1905</date>,
                  since then they became a close scholarly colleque until <persName ref="PRS7453NaffaW">Naffāʿ Wad ʿƎtmān</persName> disappeared  in<date>1910</date>.
               </floruit>
                  
